(version 1)
;; AC-4 macOS OS-deny profile (ADR-0027 / #138). A kernel-enforced Seatbelt
;; sandbox that DENIES all network for the wrapped process tree (children and
;; worker threads inherit it), allowing only loopback so local IPC and on-device
;; compute are unaffected. This is the macOS equivalent of the Linux iptables
;; default-DROP: it is what gives the real, shipped whisper-cli ZERO off-machine
;; egress while it transcribes a fixture WAV, and what blocks the routable-target
;; positive controls. `sandbox-exec` needs no sudo or firewall service, so it
;; runs reliably on hosted runners (verified: a routable probe is dropped, the
;; binary still produces JFK's words).
;;
;; Residual gap (see DECISIONS.md ADR-0027): Seatbelt's `remote ip` host filter
;; accepts only `*` or `localhost`, never an arbitrary remote host, so this layer
;; cannot express "deny all egress EXCEPT the pinned model host". The only-pinned
;; -GET model download stays proven at the webRequest allowlist (unit-tested) and
;; the Linux deny-all backstop, not at this OS layer.
(allow default)
(deny network*)
(allow network-outbound (remote ip "localhost:*"))
(allow network-inbound (local ip "localhost:*"))
